      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Estimate the chemical shift of each carbon in the following molecule. Predict which carbons will appear in the DEPT-90 spectrum, which will give positive peaks in the DEPT-135 spectrum, and which will give negative peaks in the DEPT-135 spectrum.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa3NVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--20b4117280f915cd42acbbef74e783f058b9f2dd/OChem_13_12_004.jpg\" alt=\"The ball-and-stick model has a 6-carbon chain with double bond between C 2-C 3. C 2 is bonded to methoxy group. C 4 is carbonyl group.\">",
